question: Sneak peek?
answer:
Of the one-shot turned actual story?  Of course!! 

The prompt was Penny is a Stark Industries Intern and (secretly) Spidergirl.  She gets close to the Avengers, especially Tony Stark, and the story is going to be kind of like my Whumptober one-shot: Bruises.  

“Excuse me!  Hey, you!”  Penny paused on her way out, turning to find a young woman dressed in heels and a pencil skirt staring at her, juggling two to-go cupholders with four cups each, what looked like six plastic bags hanging off her arms, and a clipboard. 

“Oh…right.  Sorry.”  Penny took a hesitant step forward, not sure where to start.

“For god’s sake, temp.”  The woman snapped.  “Pay attention.  Where were you even going?”

“Um…home?”

“Home?  Don’t you read your email?”

“What?”

“The meeting!”  Penny took one of the coffee cup holders and then the other, blinking in surprise when the woman loaded her down with the bags too, hanging them off of her arms.  It wasn’t exactly heavy…she did have super strength after all.  But it was awkward to try and carry everything without spilling the cups of coffee all over herself. “Miss Potts is waiting for these in conference room A.”

“What?”  Penny asked, feeling like she’d stumbled into a nightmare.  Like she was in a play but couldn’t figure out her lines.  

“Seriously?  Look, take the elevator…”. She led Penny over by the elbow, swiped her own pass and hit the button to floor 72…the level that required Avenger level access.  “Conference room A.  The meeting is starting in less than five minutes, so you’d better hurry.”

“Wait…I’m not…”. And then the elevator doors were closing.  “Shit.”

The doors opened to floor 73, and Penny took a hesitant step out into the hallway.  There were no doors in the immediate vicinity…no signs or arrows.  Groaning, she took a careful step to the right, doing her best not to jostle the coffees.  They were hot…she could tell just from brushing up against one with her arm. But walking all the way to the edge of the hall, she didn’t see any doors.  There were keypads set into the wall…but no doors.

She heard footsteps then, and her heart leaped into her throat.  She wasn’t even supposed to be up here!  But she needed to get this stuff dropped off!  She hurried in the direction of the footsteps, pausing when she turned the corner and nearly ran right into someone.  “I’m so sorry!”  She cried, jumping back and staring up at an unfamiliar face.  Well…mostly unfamiliar.  She might have seen him somewhere.  Regardless, he stared down at her in confusion and some suspicion.  Deciding to just bite the bullet, she spoke in a rush.

“Can you please help me?”

“Sure, kid.  What do you need?”  He asked, eyes straying down to the bags hanging from her arms.  

“The lady down in the lobby told me to take this up to conference room A and she told me that I had to hurry and that the meeting started in five minutes but I think she thought I was someone else because I don’t think I’m even supposed to be down here but I didn’t want to just leave this stuff…”. She trailed off and the man smiled a little.  

“Do you work here, kid?”

“Yes…I mean…I’m an intern.  Down in research and development mostly…”. He nodded.  

“Alright.  Hand me that.”  He reached out, taking one of the to-go cupholders.

“Oh…you don’t have to…”

“Don’t worry about it.  Come on.  I’ll show you where the conference room is.”  

“Thank you so much, sir.”  She released a breath, scurrying after him.

“What’s your name, kid?”

“Oh.  Um…Penny, sir.  Penny Parker.”

“It’s nice to meet you, Penny.  I’m Clint.”  He called over his shoulder.  And, placing his hand on the keypad, he revealed a door that suddenly appeared in the wall.  “Sorry I’m late but I found the coffee…and some kid.”  Feeling her face flush, she took a step into the room, breath catching as her eyes went around the table.  

At the head, facing her, was Pepper Potts.  The Pepper Potts.  As in, her boss’s boss’s boss’s boss’s boss.  Heck, there may need to be more rungs in that ladder!  Standing beside the window was Tony Stark who had just turned away from his conversation with Steve Rogers.  Captain America and Iron Man were staring at her from beside the window of a secret conference room on a floor she wasn’t even allowed to be on.
